
                         JPA Example using Java Beans

There are 4 main implementations of JPA: Hibernate, OpenJPA (Apache), Toplink Essentials and Eclipselink.
There is a comparison of the 4 implementations. None were the best in everything.

The following are required by a JPA program:

persistence.xml            The configuration file. This must be in META-INF.
nu.Student, nu.Course      Examples of data classes using properties.
Test                       Example of a test program that stores objects and then retrieves them.

mysql-connector-java.jar           MySQL driver. Other drivers and databases can be used. Specify the driver in the configuration.
geronimo-jpa_2.0_spec-1.1.jar      JPA API Version 2.0
openjpa-2.0.1.jar                  Main OpenJPA component
commons-lang-2.1.jar               Various extensions to the Java class library
commons-collections-3.2.1.jar      Extension of the Java Collections Framework
geronimo-jta_1.1_spec-1.1.1.jar    Apache transaction processing support
serp-1.13.1.jar                    Java bytecode manipulation (similar to javassist)
